1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,962
[NEWS ANCHOR] <i>A rescue team</i>
<i>has been deployed to La Playa Roja.</i>

2
00:00:04,045 --> 00:00:08,049
<i>One of the hostages is the son</i>
<i>of Senator Eduardo Maristella,</i>

3
00:00:08,133 --> 00:00:09,551
<i>Macky Maristella.</i>

4
00:00:09,634 --> 00:00:10,885
<i>So what are you planning to do?</i>

5
00:00:10,969 --> 00:00:14,848
<i>We will not give in</i>
<i>to the demands of the hostage takers.</i>

6
00:00:14,931 --> 00:00:18,810
<i>There's so much happening, Ma.</i>
<i>I don't know who to trust anymore.</i>

7
00:00:18,893 --> 00:00:20,687
<i>But trust me, I will make sure</i>

8
00:00:20,770 --> 00:00:24,816
<i>everyone responsible for</i>
<i>what's happening now pays the price.</i>

9
00:00:25,817 --> 00:00:28,111
<i>Son, your wound.</i>

10
00:00:28,194 --> 00:00:31,781
[WENDY]
<i>I hope you'll stop feeling angry at Greta.</i>

11
00:00:31,865 --> 00:00:35,410
<i>I know you're thinking</i>
<i>that what she did to me was wrong.</i>

12
00:00:35,493 --> 00:00:38,038
<i>But remember,</i>
<i>what I did to her was also wrong.</i>

13
00:00:38,121 --> 00:00:39,456
[MAGNUS] <i>It wasn't just you.</i>

14
00:00:39,539 --> 00:00:40,623
<i>It was both of us.</i>

15
00:00:44,252 --> 00:00:46,838
- [OLSEN]<i> Ice, what's wrong?</i>
<i>- Liam's wound won't stop bleeding.</i>

16
00:00:46,921 --> 00:00:47,964
<i>Let's go.</i>

17
00:00:48,548 --> 00:00:50,759
<i>- You've got this.</i>
<i>- We're gonna stop the bleeding.</i>

18
00:00:50,842 --> 00:00:52,051
[ICE] <i>Don't worry.</i>

19
00:00:52,135 --> 00:00:53,428
<i>- I'm right here.</i>
<i>- Okay.</i>

20
00:01:02,353 --> 00:01:06,483
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYS]

21
00:01:11,905 --> 00:01:13,031
Greta.

22
00:01:13,698 --> 00:01:15,617
How's Liam?

23
00:01:16,159 --> 00:01:17,577
Is he feeling better?

24
00:01:22,332 --> 00:01:25,543
Greta, can we have a proper conversation?

25
00:01:26,586 --> 00:01:27,712
[GRETA] What for?

26
00:01:28,296 --> 00:01:32,801
What did you mean when you said
I did something in the past

27
00:01:34,010 --> 00:01:37,222
that could have destroyed your family?

28
00:01:38,097 --> 00:01:42,936
What other sins do you think
I could have committed against you?

29
00:01:44,229 --> 00:01:45,396
"Think"?

30
00:01:46,064 --> 00:01:48,566
So you believe it's all in my head?

31
00:01:49,901 --> 00:01:54,697
Everyone blamed me
for your ten years in prison.

32
00:01:55,448 --> 00:01:57,408
My husband included.

33
00:01:57,492 --> 00:01:59,077
But what they don't know is that

34
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,745
you deserve it.

35
00:02:01,329 --> 00:02:03,373
You're worse than Ayen

36
00:02:03,456 --> 00:02:06,209
and all of my husband's
former flings combined.

37
00:02:07,335 --> 00:02:09,045
But even that is an understatement.

38
00:02:10,130 --> 00:02:11,589
[VOICE BREAKING] Because you…

39
00:02:12,632 --> 00:02:14,175
You were my friend.

40
00:02:15,009 --> 00:02:17,220
My best friend.

41
00:02:17,303 --> 00:02:20,473
Yet you still went after my husband.

42
00:02:20,557 --> 00:02:23,226
That makes you the lowest of them all!

43
00:02:23,309 --> 00:02:24,811
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

44
00:02:24,894 --> 00:02:26,354
Did you seriously think

45
00:02:27,522 --> 00:02:29,232
I didn't catch you two?

46
00:02:29,315 --> 00:02:31,442
That I don't know
what happened between you?

47
00:02:33,403 --> 00:02:34,779
[WENDY BREATHES DEEPLY]

48
00:02:34,863 --> 00:02:36,698
Greta, let me-- Let me explain.

49
00:02:36,781 --> 00:02:37,949
Explain what?

50
00:02:38,992 --> 00:02:40,326
That you two were just drunk?

51
00:02:41,536 --> 00:02:44,414
I've been holding it in
for far too long, Wendy.

52
00:02:45,582 --> 00:02:47,417
I've just been letting it slide.

53
00:02:48,334 --> 00:02:51,588
But I can see it, I can feel it--

54
00:02:51,671 --> 00:02:54,632
You still want to take
my husband away from me!

55
00:02:55,216 --> 00:02:57,302
- That's not true--
- Liar!

56
00:02:57,385 --> 00:02:58,803
Traitor!

57
00:02:58,887 --> 00:03:02,765
- [MAGNUS] Greta! Greta, that's enough!
- [WENDY BREATHES SHARPLY]

58
00:03:02,849 --> 00:03:04,142
- [EXCLAIMS]
- Greta!

59
00:03:04,225 --> 00:03:06,811
- [BREATHING HEAVILY]
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

60
00:03:06,895 --> 00:03:08,605
[GRETA SOBBING]

61
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:11,566
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

62
00:03:11,649 --> 00:03:16,404
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

63
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:18,615
[WENDY SNIFFLES]

64
00:03:18,698 --> 00:03:24,996
[CRYING]

65
00:03:33,296 --> 00:03:38,635
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

66
00:04:13,461 --> 00:04:19,884
You didn't hesitate to take the blame
for Ma'am Greta

67
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:23,388
because you were feeling guilty.

68
00:04:23,471 --> 00:04:27,850
- [MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]
- [CRYING SOFTLY]

69
00:04:27,934 --> 00:04:29,477
For my son.

70
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:31,646
[ROOSTER CROWING IN THE DISTANCE]

71
00:04:31,729 --> 00:04:34,357
For one night of weakness.

72
00:04:37,110 --> 00:04:42,448
And you paid for it with ten years.

73
00:04:42,532 --> 00:04:45,702
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

74
00:04:45,785 --> 00:04:48,663
What happened between you and Magnus…

75
00:04:49,414 --> 00:04:52,583
Was that why you left La Playa Roja?

76
00:04:52,667 --> 00:04:54,043
[WENDY SNIFFLES]

77
00:04:56,296 --> 00:05:00,216
I didn't want to come between
Magnus and Greta.

78
00:05:04,679 --> 00:05:07,515
[VOICE BREAKS]
But when Olsen got run over…

79
00:05:07,598 --> 00:05:10,143
[SNIFFLING, RAGGED BREATHS]

80
00:05:10,226 --> 00:05:12,437
I was desperate.

81
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:14,647
I turned to Greta.

82
00:05:16,649 --> 00:05:19,777
And that was her chance
to get back at you.

83
00:05:19,861 --> 00:05:23,239
I don't want to think
she's taking revenge on me.

84
00:05:24,866 --> 00:05:27,327
After all, I'm guilty too.

85
00:05:29,412 --> 00:05:30,580
Because

86
00:05:31,789 --> 00:05:34,625
you still love your friend's husband.

87
00:05:34,709 --> 00:05:38,504
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

88
00:05:39,756 --> 00:05:41,799
[GRETA CRYING QUIETLY]

89
00:05:44,844 --> 00:05:47,138
Everyone's life is in danger.

90
00:05:48,389 --> 00:05:49,932
Why would you do this?

91
00:05:53,061 --> 00:05:55,396
Can't you see what Wendy is doing?

92
00:05:56,022 --> 00:05:58,274
She's tearing us apart, Magnus.

93
00:05:58,858 --> 00:06:00,610
You don't know what you're talking about.

94
00:06:00,693 --> 00:06:04,655
I know she was your first love.
Am I right?

95
00:06:04,739 --> 00:06:05,656
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

96
00:06:05,740 --> 00:06:07,158
I married you.

97
00:06:07,241 --> 00:06:09,118
Because I got pregnant.

98
00:06:10,536 --> 00:06:13,247
I married you out of love.

99
00:06:14,290 --> 00:06:16,292
We loved you both at the same time,

100
00:06:16,375 --> 00:06:20,046
so I know exactly what's on Wendy's mind.

101
00:06:20,129 --> 00:06:22,924
She thinks I stole you from her.

102
00:06:23,007 --> 00:06:25,676
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

103
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:30,598
She even tried to take you
back from me then!

104
00:06:33,184 --> 00:06:35,061
I saw you together, Magnus.

105
00:06:36,395 --> 00:06:38,314
I saw you!

106
00:06:40,441 --> 00:06:44,570
<i>I didn't mean for that to happen.</i>

107
00:06:45,321 --> 00:06:46,405
<i>But…</i>

108
00:06:46,489 --> 00:06:49,450
<i>I wanted it to happen.</i>

109
00:06:49,534 --> 00:06:51,410
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

110
00:06:51,494 --> 00:06:54,205
<i>Do you feel the same way too?</i>

111
00:06:54,997 --> 00:06:56,290
[WENDY EXHALES DEEPLY]

112
00:06:59,460 --> 00:07:01,254
<i>But this is wrong.</i>

113
00:07:02,588 --> 00:07:04,340
<i>We can't do this.</i>

114
00:07:10,346 --> 00:07:12,640
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

115
00:07:12,723 --> 00:07:14,142
[WENDY]<i> Uh…</i>

116
00:07:16,310 --> 00:07:17,353
<i>We can't.</i>

117
00:07:17,895 --> 00:07:20,106
<i>Magnus, this isn't right.</i>

118
00:07:20,857 --> 00:07:22,942
<i>None of this is right.</i>

119
00:07:29,323 --> 00:07:33,369
I kept what I knew
about what happened a secret

120
00:07:35,079 --> 00:07:36,747
because I was afraid

121
00:07:38,291 --> 00:07:41,335
that if I confronted you two…

122
00:07:41,419 --> 00:07:43,337
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

123
00:07:43,421 --> 00:07:45,465
…about your affair,

124
00:07:45,548 --> 00:07:47,091
you would choose her.

125
00:07:49,093 --> 00:07:50,970
But maybe it was for the best

126
00:07:51,762 --> 00:07:53,764
that she left on her own.

127
00:07:53,848 --> 00:07:55,933
But you accepted her back.

128
00:07:57,226 --> 00:07:58,936
When she asked you for help.

129
00:08:01,731 --> 00:08:03,566
That's because

130
00:08:03,649 --> 00:08:05,276
that was your chance, right?

131
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:07,612
To get back at her?

132
00:08:07,695 --> 00:08:10,323
And I don't regret a thing

133
00:08:11,949 --> 00:08:14,243
about her ending up in prison
for something that I did!

134
00:08:14,869 --> 00:08:17,788
She should've rotted in prison!

135
00:08:17,872 --> 00:08:19,540
Now that she's free,

136
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:21,751
she's destroying us again.

137
00:08:21,834 --> 00:08:24,378
Greta, you are very paranoid.

138
00:08:24,462 --> 00:08:26,881
What Wendy and I had was a long time ago.

139
00:08:26,964 --> 00:08:27,965
It's in the past now.

140
00:08:28,049 --> 00:08:29,509
It's over.

141
00:08:30,134 --> 00:08:31,552
For you, it's over.

142
00:08:31,636 --> 00:08:33,095
But you can't say the same about Wendy.

143
00:08:33,179 --> 00:08:35,723
I can see it. I can feel it.

144
00:08:35,806 --> 00:08:37,600
She's no different from Ayen.

145
00:08:37,683 --> 00:08:41,062
She won't stop chasing you
even if you try to break free.

146
00:08:41,145 --> 00:08:42,647
Even me…

147
00:08:43,439 --> 00:08:45,566
Even I'm being threatened.

148
00:08:45,650 --> 00:08:48,319
[THROUGH GRITTED TEETH] Can you
stop mentioning Ayen's name?

149
00:08:48,402 --> 00:08:49,654
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

150
00:08:49,737 --> 00:08:51,239
[WHISPERS] No Ayen.

151
00:08:52,031 --> 00:08:53,241
[GRETA SCOFFS]

152
00:08:55,117 --> 00:08:55,993
Look.

153
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:59,872
We promised each other

154
00:09:00,623 --> 00:09:03,376
that we would stay strong, remember?

155
00:09:03,459 --> 00:09:05,336
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

156
00:09:05,419 --> 00:09:07,880
After everything we've been through.

157
00:09:07,964 --> 00:09:10,132
Everything that's happened to us now.

158
00:09:11,467 --> 00:09:14,679
Especially after we almost lost Liam.

159
00:09:16,013 --> 00:09:17,723
[GRETA CRYING QUIETLY]

160
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:20,434
I admit it.

161
00:09:21,602 --> 00:09:25,523
I was very disappointed in you
when I found out what you did to Wendy.

162
00:09:26,190 --> 00:09:29,527
Of course I'm also angry
because of the 300 million you--

163
00:09:30,736 --> 00:09:32,488
Okay. I'm sorry.

164
00:09:33,322 --> 00:09:34,740
That's done.

165
00:09:35,783 --> 00:09:40,913
What I'm trying to tell you, Greta,
is that I'm willing to forgive you

166
00:09:40,997 --> 00:09:43,082
so we can move on.

167
00:09:45,501 --> 00:09:49,213
I also want to apologize to you.

168
00:09:51,007 --> 00:09:54,135
Greta, I'm sorry for what happened
between me and Wendy.

169
00:09:56,387 --> 00:09:57,555
Please,

170
00:09:58,347 --> 00:10:00,933
can we please just leave that in the past?

171
00:10:03,603 --> 00:10:05,813
What matters now

172
00:10:07,690 --> 00:10:10,651
is that we survive this as a family.

173
00:10:12,987 --> 00:10:15,948
We need each other.

174
00:10:16,032 --> 00:10:22,121
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

175
00:10:22,204 --> 00:10:23,873
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

176
00:10:24,915 --> 00:10:25,875
Okay?

177
00:10:35,259 --> 00:10:36,344
Pa.

178
00:10:37,845 --> 00:10:39,680
That's over.

179
00:10:39,764 --> 00:10:41,390
That was a long time ago.

180
00:10:41,474 --> 00:10:42,767
Why?

181
00:10:44,060 --> 00:10:46,729
Because you married another man?

182
00:10:47,396 --> 00:10:49,398
A man that

183
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:52,943
you never introduced to me.

184
00:10:53,027 --> 00:10:55,237
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

185
00:10:55,321 --> 00:10:58,032
I made a big mistake, Pa.

186
00:11:00,034 --> 00:11:04,080
I shouldn't have married
someone I barely knew.

187
00:11:04,914 --> 00:11:08,459
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

188
00:11:08,542 --> 00:11:10,878
I only found out he was a criminal
after I married him.

189
00:11:10,961 --> 00:11:13,214
That's why I left him.

190
00:11:15,758 --> 00:11:17,009
You know,

191
00:11:18,386 --> 00:11:20,763
we've been apart for a long time, dear.

192
00:11:24,683 --> 00:11:27,895
[SIGHS] I don't know you anymore.

193
00:11:27,978 --> 00:11:31,148
[WHIMPERS]

194
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:35,945
[SNIFFLES, SOBS]

195
00:11:36,028 --> 00:11:40,908
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

196
00:11:44,703 --> 00:11:46,997
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

197
00:11:58,843 --> 00:12:05,349
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

198
00:12:07,935 --> 00:12:09,228
What is it?

199
00:12:18,487 --> 00:12:21,323
- [MUSIC SWELLS]
- Something's on your face.

200
00:12:26,996 --> 00:12:28,330
[CLICKS TONGUE] You know,

201
00:12:29,540 --> 00:12:31,584
when I become a resort manager,

202
00:12:31,667 --> 00:12:34,545
well, not this resort…

203
00:12:35,296 --> 00:12:36,380
Mm?

204
00:12:36,464 --> 00:12:38,799
…I'll hire you as our official nurse.

205
00:12:38,883 --> 00:12:41,886
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

206
00:12:41,969 --> 00:12:44,805
If Liam asks me to work for him
at his other businesses,

207
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:49,852
why not, right?

208
00:12:51,854 --> 00:12:55,649
This is the first time
I've seen Liam up close.

209
00:12:56,984 --> 00:12:58,277
He's pretty cute.

210
00:12:59,111 --> 00:13:00,946
[ICE] Like…

211
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:02,781
[ICE CLICKS TONGUE]
I think

212
00:13:04,325 --> 00:13:05,367
…I have a crush on him.

213
00:13:05,451 --> 00:13:06,702
[SCOFFS] Wow.

214
00:13:07,828 --> 00:13:08,829
Unbelievable.

215
00:13:09,705 --> 00:13:15,002
You can seriously joke around
after what happened?

216
00:13:15,085 --> 00:13:17,671
Who says I'm joking?

217
00:13:17,755 --> 00:13:18,881
You like him?

218
00:13:21,008 --> 00:13:22,426
Don't you have a boyfriend?

219
00:13:23,052 --> 00:13:24,303
[SCOFFS]

220
00:13:24,386 --> 00:13:26,013
It's just a crush.

221
00:13:28,265 --> 00:13:31,393
Anyway, I've got to
check on one of my patients.

222
00:13:32,186 --> 00:13:33,395
Liam.

223
00:13:33,479 --> 00:13:40,152
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

224
00:13:48,994 --> 00:13:51,956
Mommy, Daddy, I promise…

225
00:13:52,039 --> 00:13:52,873
[MIKE] Hmm?

226
00:13:52,957 --> 00:13:56,585
…that when I went back to school,
I'll always be in the honor roll.

227
00:13:56,669 --> 00:13:58,587
- [MINNIE LAUGHS SOFTLY]
- Wow.

228
00:13:58,671 --> 00:14:02,216
What about you, Daddy?
What's your promise?

229
00:14:02,299 --> 00:14:05,010
- Hmm…
- Tell her.

230
00:14:05,094 --> 00:14:07,221
I promise

231
00:14:07,304 --> 00:14:10,391
I won't work on weekends anymore.

232
00:14:10,474 --> 00:14:11,392
[MINNIE LAUGHS SOFTLY]

233
00:14:11,475 --> 00:14:13,269
- Really, Daddy?
- Yes.

234
00:14:13,352 --> 00:14:15,312
I promise. [SMOOCHES]

235
00:14:16,105 --> 00:14:19,024
What about you, Mommy?
What's your promise?

236
00:14:20,442 --> 00:14:21,610
Hmm.

237
00:14:22,862 --> 00:14:24,780
What's my promise?

238
00:14:24,864 --> 00:14:28,701
- I'll make a promise for you.
- Okay.

239
00:14:28,784 --> 00:14:31,453
- Promise us, Mommy…
- Hmm?

240
00:14:31,537 --> 00:14:36,083
…that you'll put a medal on me
at my graduation.

241
00:14:36,166 --> 00:14:38,252
My first honor medal.

242
00:14:38,335 --> 00:14:40,212
[GIGGLES]

243
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:43,173
Okay, I promise.

244
00:14:45,175 --> 00:14:46,719
- But, Mommy…
- [MINNIE] Hmm?

245
00:14:46,802 --> 00:14:48,554
…even when I'm in college already,

246
00:14:48,637 --> 00:14:51,724
will you still be the one
to hang my medals on me?

247
00:14:56,937 --> 00:14:58,355
Mm-hmm.

248
00:15:00,566 --> 00:15:04,737
Can I just promise you

249
00:15:04,820 --> 00:15:06,572
that we'll get home safe and sound?

250
00:15:06,655 --> 00:15:08,449
Is that okay?

251
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:12,328
Yes, Mommy. We can go home now?

252
00:15:14,163 --> 00:15:17,666
We'll all go home, Maddie.

253
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:23,881
[UPLIFTING MUSIC PLAYING]

254
00:15:33,057 --> 00:15:34,308
Have some water.

255
00:15:36,727 --> 00:15:37,978
[LUNA] Dude.

256
00:15:38,062 --> 00:15:41,190
Are you sure you're good to walk?

257
00:15:41,273 --> 00:15:42,274
[CLEARS THROAT]

258
00:15:43,692 --> 00:15:46,946
I can walk, I can swim.

259
00:15:47,029 --> 00:15:48,322
I'm good.

260
00:15:49,573 --> 00:15:50,991
But what about your wound?

261
00:15:51,075 --> 00:15:52,743
What if it opens up?

262
00:15:52,826 --> 00:15:54,578
Then let it.

263
00:15:55,621 --> 00:15:58,582
Luna, after everything we've done so far,

264
00:15:58,666 --> 00:16:00,834
I feel like I can do anything.

265
00:16:00,918 --> 00:16:02,086
Promise.

266
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:05,756
Yeah, I saw.

267
00:16:05,839 --> 00:16:07,466
- [LIAM SIGHS]
- You can do anything.

268
00:16:08,926 --> 00:16:10,886
You're even capable of forgiveness.

269
00:16:14,682 --> 00:16:15,975
You're talking about Mama?

270
00:16:19,687 --> 00:16:21,021
I just told her

271
00:16:22,398 --> 00:16:24,066
I don't think I can hate her.

272
00:16:25,734 --> 00:16:26,986
I just can't.

273
00:16:40,374 --> 00:16:41,625
Olsen.

274
00:16:43,002 --> 00:16:44,503
Thank you for your help.

275
00:16:44,586 --> 00:16:45,963
[ICE] I need you to be quiet, okay?

276
00:16:46,046 --> 00:16:47,715
Put your arm up.

277
00:16:49,049 --> 00:16:50,134
Come on.

278
00:16:52,219 --> 00:16:53,262
There you go.

279
00:16:53,929 --> 00:16:56,306
We need to check your temperature

280
00:16:56,932 --> 00:16:58,767
to see if you have a fever
or an infection.

281
00:16:58,851 --> 00:17:01,061
Let's hope that's not the case.

282
00:17:01,729 --> 00:17:03,105
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

283
00:17:05,065 --> 00:17:06,066
[THERMOMETER BEEPS]

284
00:17:06,692 --> 00:17:08,318
Let me check.

285
00:17:08,402 --> 00:17:10,529
Whoo! You have no fever.

286
00:17:10,612 --> 00:17:12,823
[CLICKS TONGUE] You're gonna survive.

287
00:17:16,243 --> 00:17:17,911
[LIAM GROANS] Olsen?

288
00:17:20,205 --> 00:17:21,373
I owe you.

289
00:17:23,917 --> 00:17:26,712
If you and Papa hadn't been
at the marina earlier,

290
00:17:27,838 --> 00:17:28,922
I'd probably be gone.

291
00:17:29,006 --> 00:17:29,923
[OLSEN] No way.

292
00:17:30,966 --> 00:17:35,137
It was Ice who saved you, remember?

293
00:17:36,138 --> 00:17:37,181
Right, Ice?

294
00:17:37,264 --> 00:17:43,270
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

295
00:17:58,869 --> 00:18:05,167
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

296
00:18:06,043 --> 00:18:07,628
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

297
00:18:14,551 --> 00:18:15,969
How are things here, bro?

298
00:18:16,762 --> 00:18:18,764
All good. He's calmed down.

299
00:18:18,847 --> 00:18:20,057
He won't fight back anymore.

300
00:18:24,853 --> 00:18:26,688
Keep an eye on him, okay?

301
00:18:27,439 --> 00:18:29,108
We can still use him.

302
00:18:29,942 --> 00:18:31,693
Just in case things go sideways.

303
00:18:32,569 --> 00:18:35,197
[MUFFLED] Just kill me.

304
00:18:38,575 --> 00:18:39,535
Huh?

305
00:18:41,286 --> 00:18:42,579
What did you say?

306
00:18:49,503 --> 00:18:53,173
- [SNIFFLES]
- [SUSPENSEFUL STING]

307
00:18:53,257 --> 00:18:54,967
Just kill me already.

308
00:18:55,759 --> 00:18:57,761
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

309
00:18:57,845 --> 00:19:00,222
[WHIMPERS] I don't care anymore.

310
00:19:04,351 --> 00:19:06,562
We agreed we'd only ask for money.

311
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:09,273
[SNIFFLES]

312
00:19:09,356 --> 00:19:12,693
I betrayed my brother.
I'm sure he doesn't…

313
00:19:12,776 --> 00:19:14,820
They don't care about me anymore.

314
00:19:18,282 --> 00:19:19,783
I can't take it anymore.

315
00:19:24,371 --> 00:19:26,165
So many people have died.

316
00:19:27,958 --> 00:19:29,334
[IAN] Jules…

317
00:19:30,836 --> 00:19:32,796
We agreed we'd only ask for money.

318
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:35,215
I didn't know this would happen.

319
00:19:35,299 --> 00:19:36,925
[BREATH QUIVERING]

320
00:19:37,009 --> 00:19:38,594
You didn't know?

321
00:19:46,226 --> 00:19:48,770
You want to know why, hmm?

322
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:53,817
Because you're heartless animals.

323
00:19:56,236 --> 00:19:57,946
Do you hear me?

324
00:20:03,118 --> 00:20:04,578
[SUSPENSEFUL STING]

325
00:20:04,661 --> 00:20:11,168
[TENSE MUSIC ESCALATES]

326
00:20:14,004 --> 00:20:15,839
<i>I'm ready to go as soon as we can leave.</i>

327
00:20:15,923 --> 00:20:18,008
<i>But we're still waiting</i>
<i>for Cariaso's go signal.</i>

328
00:20:18,091 --> 00:20:19,718
[CARIASO] <i>Come in.</i>
<i>The speedboats are still here.</i>

329
00:20:19,801 --> 00:20:21,637
<i>The route here is still safe.</i>

330
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:24,306
- [MARISTELLA] <i>I just need my son back.</i>
<i>- I'll give you my word--</i>

331
00:20:24,389 --> 00:20:26,516
<i>We're talking about my son here!</i>

332
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:28,393
<i>What else do you want?!</i>
<i>You bastards!</i>

333
00:20:28,477 --> 00:20:31,146
<i>Your father has only given us cash.</i>
<i>There's something else we need.</i>

334
00:20:31,230 --> 00:20:33,732
<i>We need to start evacuating people.</i>
<i>Prepare the hostages.</i>

335
00:20:33,815 --> 00:20:35,651
<i>We'll leave the island</i>
<i>as soon as possible.</i>

336
00:20:36,526 --> 00:20:37,653
[GRETA]<i> Hello?</i>

337
00:20:37,736 --> 00:20:38,695
<i>Who are you talking to?</i>
